is for the introduction of Serious Shortage Protocols for medicine.","false","Biography information for Wayne David","Caerphilly","Wayne David","206271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037846","Prime Minister","false","2019-01-16","<p>My recent discussions with European Leaders have been primarily about matters relating to the United Kingdom leaving the EU, but also have covered other issues including with President Macron the matter of migration</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2019-01-16T16:03:02.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037846/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037846/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037846/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2019-01-08","Immigration and Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister,  whether she discussed refugees and migrants seeking to migrate to the UK during her recent meetings with European leaders.","true","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","206239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037847","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-01-16","<p>Provisional figures for 2017 show 327 badgers were vaccinated under licence from Natural England. The number of BCG doses made available for badger vaccination was limited in 2017 due to a global shortage and the need to prioritise supplies for human vaccination. Global BCG vaccine supply is now improving and although complete figures for the number of badgers vaccinated in 2018 are not yet available, provisional data returned to date indicate that the number will be higher than in 2017.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2019-01-16T17:16:06.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037847/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037847/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037847/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-01-08","Bovine Tuberculosis: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many badgers were vaccinated for TB in the last year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Julian Sturdy","York Outer","Julian Sturdy","206346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037848","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-01-11","<p>Government is continuing to assess the effect of the UK leaving the EU on the civil society sector. We are gathering information on the challenges and opportunities exiting the EU presents, and we are sharing information with, and listening to the views of civil society organisations as this work progresses. We continue to work across government to champion the sector’s views during the EU exit process and beyond.</p><p> </p>","Eastleigh","Mims Davies",,"2019-01-11T14:38:36.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037848/answer","Biography information for Mims Davies","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037848/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037848/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-01-08","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether his Department will publish the initial findings of its assessment of the effect on the civil society sector of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","206374"
