"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037918","Cabinet Office","false","2019-01-11","<p>No adverts running on the Road to Brexit Facebook page have been targeted based on postcodes, therefore this information is not available.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2019-01-11T14:16:05.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037918/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037918/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037918/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-01-08","Department for Exiting the European Union: Facebook","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer to Question 201628, what postcodes have the adverts from the Facebook page road to brexit been targeted since 21 November 2017.","false","Biography information for Stella Creasy","Walthamstow","Stella Creasy","206350"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037919","House of Commons Commission","false","2019-01-30","<p>The Commission has had no discussions with the Metropolitan Police about the closure.</p><p>Exit three from Westminster tube station has been closed until 2021 to ensure that works to conserve the Elizabeth Tower can continue safely.</p><p>This decision was taken by Parliament’s Strategic Estates Team and the appointed contractor, in close consultation with Transport for London, the Metropolitan Police and Westminster City Council. The Parliamentary Security Directorate were also consulted.</p><p>Hoardings have been erected to direct members of the public, which will remain in place throughout the duration of the project.</p><p>The closure is an additional safety measure for members of the public given the proximity of that exit to the base of the Elizabeth Tower.</p>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2019-01-30T11:30:27.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037919/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037919/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037919/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2019-01-08","Parliamentary Estate: Access","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington, representing the House of Commons Commission, what discussions the Commission has had with the Metropolitan Police on the closure of the Bridge street subway exit at Westminster tube station.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","206394"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037920","Cabinet Office","false","2019-01-11","<p>The issue of electoral voting rights is part of the wider issue of the rights of EU citizens and UK expats that need to be considered during the Brexit preparations. The rights of both sides should be taken together. The UK pushed hard in negotiations for reciprocal voting rights for EU citizens in the UK, and UK nationals in the EU, but they will not form part of the Withdrawal Agreement. The Government has made clear that we will seek to discuss this issue bilaterally with individual Member States with a view to protecting the rights of UK nationals resident in those Member States, where they will not otherwise continue.</p><p>We do not anticipate any changes to the current UK primary legislative framework for candidacy and voting rights being made before the May 2019 English and Northern Ireland local elections. The Scottish Parliament and Welsh Assembly are responsible for their own franchises.</p><p>To provide certainty to prospective candidates, it will be the policy intent of the UK Government that candidates who are validly nominated and elected at or before the May 2019 local elections in England and Northern Ireland should be able to serve that term of office in full, notwithstanding any wider changes to voting and candidacy rights in the future.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2019-01-11T13:59:43.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037920/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037920/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037920/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-01-08","Voting Rights: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if the Government will take steps to ensure the voting rights of citizens of other EU member states in local elections under all possible scenarios after March 2019.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","206378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037921","Department for Education","false","2019-01-16","<p>There was no requirement to undertake a public consultation.</p><p>To consider making an amendment to the regulations (under section 122 of the Education Act 2002), the Secretary of State must consult with those as appear to [him/her] to be appropriate to consult having regard to the content of the order.</p><p> </p><p>To meet the requirement and the commitment set out in the early years workforce strategy we consulted with the relevant stakeholders the department regularly consults under this section of the Education Act 2002 – Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector, unions and bodies representing the interests of governing bodies of schools, school and college leaders and teachers.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2019-01-16T11:55:23.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037921/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037921/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037921/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-01-08","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the letter of 18 July 2018 from the Minister of State for Children and Families to the Chair of the Education Select Committee on that Committee’s Life Chances inquiry, for what reasons he did not undertake a full public consultation on amending regulations to enable people with Early Years Professional Status and Early Years Teacher Status to lead nursery classes in maintained settings; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","206298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037922","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-01-11","<p>This information is not held.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2019-01-11T13:09:18.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037922/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037922/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037922/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-08","Dentistry: Fines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 4 September 2018 to Question 167266, how many FP17 forms have not been accepted by the NHS Business Services Authority due to concerns about the address provided for the patient.","false","Biography information for Stella Creasy","Walthamstow","Stella Creasy","206351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037923","Department for Education","false","2019-01-16","<p>The analysis of the consultation feedback is contained within policy advice to ministers. The majority of the feedback did not support the proposed regulation change on the basis that it would not lead to parity in the pay and conditions for between those holding Early Years Professional Status/Early Years Teachers Status and teachers with Qualified Teacher Status (QTS).</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2019-01-16T11:52:03.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037923/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037923/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037923/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-01-08","Pre-school Education: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the letter of 18 July 2018 from the Minister of State for Children and Families to the Chair of the Education Select Committee on that Committee’s Life Chances inquiry, if he will place in the Library a copy of his analysis of the written consultation undertaken with those relevant stakeholders his Department regularly consults under the relevant section of the Education Act 2002 on amending regulations to enable people with Early Years Professional Status and Early Years Teacher Status to lead nursery classes in maintained settings.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","206299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037924","Cabinet Office","false","2019-01-14","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2019-01-14T17:14:40.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037924/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037924/answer","PQ206379 (2).pdf","UKSA Response","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037924/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-01-08","Offences against Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of crimes committed against children in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","206379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037925","Home Office","false","2019-01-24","<p>The general position is that if information is given in circumstances where it is expected that a duty of confidence applies, that information cannot normally be disclosed without the information provider's consent.</p><p>Three circumstances making disclosure of confidential information lawful are:</p><p>• where the individual to whom the information relates has consented;<br>• where disclosure is in the public interest; and<br>• where there is a legal duty to do so, for example a court order.</p><p>So, under the common law, a healthcare provider wishing to disclose a patient's personal information to anyone outside the team providing care should first seek the consent of that patient.</p><p>There are legal gateways for sharing data and the Police and Criminal Evidence Act 1984 (PACE and Codes issued under the Act). These include a range of explicit and implied powers enabling the police to seek and share information, in pursuit of their policing purposes, including preventing a crime and protecting persons from harm.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2019-01-24T17:40:35.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037925/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037925/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037925/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-01-08","Criminal Investigation: Medical Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the Government has plans to ensure police forces can access the medical records of suspects in (a) rape, (b) transmitted disease, (c) grievous bodily harm with intent and (d) other cases.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","206380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037926","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-01-16","<p>All victims of crime are entitled to receive appropriate support to help them, as far as possible, cope and recover. Under the Code of Practice for Victims of Crime (Victims’ Code), the police must conduct a needs assessment of a victim and refer them to victim support services, unless the victim chooses not to be. This may include referral to services which specialise in supporting people diagnosed with HIV and sexual transmission of infections.</p><p> </p><p>In the Victims Strategy, published in September last year, we committed to consulting on a revised Victims’ Code to ensure that the entitlements better reflect victims’ needs.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2019-01-16T17:12:44.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037926/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037926/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037926/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-01-08","Infectious Diseases: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans the Government has to ensure that people reporting crimes involving the deliberate infection of (a) HIV and (b) other diseases can access specialised support services whilst investigations are undertaken and completed.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","206381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037927","Home Office","false","2019-01-24","<p>There is no specific offence of deliberately transmitting a sexual disease. This behaviour can be charged under Sections 18 and 20 of the Offences Against the Person Act 1861.</p><p>There are no current plans to make persons convicted of these offences subject to notification requirements (commonly referred to as being placed on the Sex Offenders Register).</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-01-24T17:51:54.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037927/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037927/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037927/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-01-08","Sexually Transmitted Infections: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the Government has any plans to ensure that people sentenced for deliberately transmitting sexual diseases to other people are placed on the sex offenders' register.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","206382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037928","Home Office","true","2019-01-24","<p><del class="ministerial">There is no specific offence of deliberately transmitting a sexual disease. This behaviour can be charged under Sections 18 and 20 of the Offences Against the Person Act 1861.</del></p><p><del class="ministerial">There are no current plans to make persons convicted of these offences subject to notification requirements (commonly referred to as being placed on the Sex Offenders Register).</del></p><p><ins class="ministerial">Where an allegation is made to the police of deliberate transmission of a sexual disease, the police already have powers to investigate under Sections 18 and 20 of the Offences Against the Person Act 1861.</ins></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2019-01-24T17:44:42.137Z","2019-01-28T15:29:11.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037928/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037928/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037928/answer","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037928/answer/previousversion/97338","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-01-08","Sexually Transmitted Infections: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the Government has plans to provide police with additional powers police to assist investigations into cases involving the deliberate transmission of sexual diseases.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","206383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037929","Home Office","false","2019-01-16","<p>We will continue to run the EU Settlement Scheme in the event of a ‘no deal’ scenario, for EU citizens resident in the UK by 29 March 2019.</p><p>As confirmed by the policy paper “Citizens’ Rights – EU citizens in the UK and UK nationals in the EU” published by the Department for Exiting the European Union on 6 December 2018, the basis for qualifying for status under the scheme will remain the same as proposed in a ‘deal’ scenario and will be focused on residence in the UK. This means that any EU citizen living in the UK by 29 March 2019 will be eligible to apply to the scheme, securing their status in UK law</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-01-16T16:35:19.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037929/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037929/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037929/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-01-08","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the settled status scheme will apply in the event of the UK leaving the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","206384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037930","Home Office","false","2019-01-16","<p>The statutory code of practice and guidance published on gov.uk <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/right-to-work-checks-employers-guide" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/right-to-work-checks-employers-guide</a> is clear that employers already need to carry out right to work checks on EU citizens, as they do with all prospective employees to prevent illegal working.</p><p>Current arrangements, under which EU citizens can demonstrate their right to work in the UK by producing their national passport or identity card, will continue after the UK leaves the European Union until the future border and immigration system is introduced. The White Paper <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/766465/The-UKs-future-skills-based-immigration-system-print-ready.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/766465/The-UKs-future-skills-based-immigration-system-print-ready.pdf</a> on the future immigration system is clear that when we move to the future system, we will not require employers to undertake retrospective right to work checks on existing EU employees.</p><p>Employers will not be required to distinguish between those who arrived before and after March 2019.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-01-16T16:13:27.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037930/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037930/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037930/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-01-08","Migrant Workers: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what advice the Government is providing to employers on employing non-UK EU nationals in the event of the UK leaving the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","206385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037931","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-01-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my predecessor (Guto Bebb) on 26 January 2018 to Question 123641 to the hon. Member for Brentford and Isleworth (Ruth Cadbury).</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2019-01-15T15:41:10.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037931/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037931/answer","Hansard  Extract  26 January 2018, UIN 123641.docx","123641 - Warships","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037931/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-01-08","HMS Vengeance and HMS Vigilant: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the need to refuel (a) HMS Vigilant and (b) HMS Vengeance in their remaining years of service.","false","Biography information for Emma Dent Coad","Kensington","Emma Dent Coad","206472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037932","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-01-16","<p>The PWR2 Naval Reactor Safety Case is a live document which is maintained through-life to justify and ensure continued safe operation of the reactors in our submarines. It is a requirement that a major stand alone review of each Safety Case is undertaken at approximately ten-year intervals. The last periodic full review was completed in 2014.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2019-01-16T15:47:26.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037932/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037932/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037932/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-01-08","Nuclear Reactors: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on what dates safety cases for the operation of the PWR2 Steam Raising Plant were submitted by his Department for regulatory approval.","false","Biography information for Emma Dent Coad","Kensington","Emma Dent Coad","206473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037933","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-01-15","<p>As of 11 January 2019, Departmental records indicate that since 1 July 2017 (a) 473 written parliamentary questions and (b) 8 Oral Parliamentary Questions, tabled to my Department by Members of both Houses, for which a different answering body was responsible, were transferred to the correct answering body.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2019-01-15T15:58:39.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037933/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037933/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037933/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037933/answer/previousversion/94804","Biography information for James Brokenshire","7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-01-08","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Parliamentary Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many times his Department has transferred (a) a Written Parliamentary Question and (b) an Oral Parliamentary Question to a different Department since July 2017.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","206288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037934","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-01-16","<p>The safety of the United Kingdom's submarine force remains our highest priority. We continue to work closely with the independent regulators to ensure the safety of operations both alongside and at sea. I am withholding further details as their disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","206475","2019-01-16T15:48:32.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037934/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037934/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037934/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-01-08","Trident Submarines: Nuclear Reactors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what contingency plans he has put in place to monitor the integrity of the fuel elements in Vanguard submarine reactors.","false","Biography information for Emma Dent Coad","Kensington","Emma Dent Coad","206474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037935","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-01-11","<p>Whilst current probate fees are determined based on an assessment of unit costing at a service level, the Ministry of Justice has not made any assessment specifically on the costs to HMCTS of administering an application for probate for estates of £5,000, £50,000 or £2 million.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2019-01-11T14:27:10.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037935/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037935/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037935/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-01-08","Probate","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what recent assessment he has made of the average cost of administering probate for an estate valued at (a) £5,000 (b) £50,0000 and (c) £2 million; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","206229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037936","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-01-16","<p>The safety of the United Kingdom's submarine force remains our highest priority. We continue to work closely with the independent regulators to ensure the safety of operations both alongside and at sea. I am withholding further details as their disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","206474","2019-01-16T15:48:32.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037936/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037936/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037936/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-01-08","Trident Submarines: Nuclear Reactors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what contingency plans he has put in place for fuel element breaches in a Vanguard submarine reactor.","false","Biography information for Emma Dent Coad","Kensington","Emma Dent Coad","206475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037937","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-01-11","<p>BT contracted over £388 million to deliver Superfast broadband within the 44 BDUK approved phase one projects. A number of these contracts are still in delivery and expected to generate efficiency savings. The amount the supplier has to contribute will not diminish from the contracted value.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2019-01-11T12:25:48.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037937/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037937/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037937/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-01-08","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what information his Department holds on the amount BT has paid in direct capital contributions to local authorities in relation to each of its 44 BDUK-approved projects.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","206211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037938","Department for Education","false","2019-01-11","<p>Given the ongoing criminal investigation, the department does not intend to publish a list of local authorities who have commissioned services from Trimega Laboratories Limited during the period of January 2010 and April 2014.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2019-01-11T13:16:26.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037938/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037938/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037938/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-01-08","Trimega","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of the 20 November 2018 to Written Question 191957 on Trimega, if he will list the local authorities identified as having commissioned tests by Trimega.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","206410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037939","Department for International Development","false","2019-01-15","<p>The Government of Japan, as hosts of the 2020 Summit, have stated that they see the Summit providing opportunities for civil society organisations. They are also open to promoting the active involvement of young people throughout. The Government of Japan is also already in dialogue with civil society on preparations for the Summit. The UK, which is working closely with the Government of Japan on Summit preparations, has encouraged and facilitated this dialogue and will continue to do so.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2019-01-15T15:32:04.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037939/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037939/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1037939/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-01-08","Developing Countries: Nutrition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what opportunities will be made for civil society organisations for young people to contribute to discussions on the nutrition for growth summit in 2020.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","206450"
